We recommended that the Management:

facilitate the appraisal of the road lots components to be recorded as part of the Road Network System;


facilitate the completion of the road map to be maintained by the GSO;


instruct the GSO and Municipal Accountant to reconcile the local road inventory report and road map with the Accounting records;



direct the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant of the complete description and cost segregation of the road networks; and

require the Municipal Accountant to do alternative procedures in determining unrecorded Road Networks like reconciling the accounting records with the roadmap. For the amount to be transferred to the accounting records, the guidelines of COA Circular 2015-008 should be observed.

